{[%evp 0,81,12,29,19,-14,-14,-24,-26,-17,-17,-24,-2,-19,-5,-3,-2,-9,-2,7,36,41,
58,27,56,65,69,68,110,97,95,103,118,115,105,104,112,91,86,100,126,132,149,144,
138,132,146,134,134,144,144,144,137,132,129,130,130,127,133,129,144,140,149,
121,128,122,129,137,171,188,233,235,231,247,260,268,265,260,259,270,269,273,
275,272]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 dxc4 5. Qa4+ (5. Nf3 {is the
modern main line.}) 5... Nbd7 6. Qxc4 c5 7. Nf3 a6 {With the idea b7-b5 and
Bc8-b7.} 8. Qc2 $1 cxd4 $2 {Now the bishop on g2 becomes very active.} ({
The most reliable answer for Black was} 8... b6 {, for example:} 9. Ne5 Nd5 10.
Nc3 Bb7 11. Nxd5 exd5 12. O-O Be7 13. Rd1 O-O 14. Qf5 Nxe5 15. dxe5 Ra7 {
with equality, 0-1 Huebner,R (2630)-Smyslov,V (2565)/Tilburg 1982/MCD (57)}) 9.
Nxd4 Qb6 ({The other possibility is} 9... Bc5 10. Nb3 Bd6 (10... Ba7 $6 11. O-O
O-O 12. Bd2 $1 Qe7 13. a3 $1 Re8 14. Bb4 Qd8 15. Nc3 {is weaker, 1-0 Smyslov,
V-Kan,I/ Leningrad 1947/URS-ch (41)}) 11. O-O O-O 12. Nc3 Rb8 13. Rd1 Qe7 14.
Be3 $14 {1-0 Speelman,J (2490)-Li Zunian (2270)/Luzern 1982/EXT 1997 (30)}) 10.
Nb3 Bb4+ 11. Bd2 ({Also good is} 11. Nc3) 11... Nc5 $2 {A bad move.} ({Perhaps
a better choice was} 11... a5 {although White maintains the pressure after} 12.
O-O a4 13. Bxb4 Qxb4 14. N3d2 O-O 15. Nc3 Ne5 16. a3 Qa5 17. Rfd1 {1-0
Andersson,U (2590)-Dominguez Sanz,J (2295)/Las Palmas 1980/EXT 2000 (30)}) 12.
O-O Nxb3 13. Qxb3 Bc5 14. Qxb6 Bxb6 15. Na3 $1 {Black´s development is
impeded, and White enjoys a tremendous queenside initiative.} Nd5 16. e4 (16.
Nc4 Bc7 17. Rac1 {was also strong , with the idea of Ne3.}) 16... Ne7 17. Bc3
O-O 18. Nc4 Bc7 19. Rfd1 Nc6 (19... b5 {can be met by} 20. e5 Rb8 (20... Nd5
21. Bxd5 exd5 22. Ne3) 21. Ba5 $1 Bxa5 (21... bxc4 $2 22. Bxc7 Rxb2 23. Bd6 Nd5
24. Bxf8 Kxf8 25. Rab1 $18) 22. Nxa5 $16) 20. e5 $1 {[%cal Gg2b7]} f6 {This
creates new weaknesses, but Black has a very difficult position anyway.} 21. f4
Rb8 22. Rac1 fxe5 23. Nxe5 $1 {The exchange of light pieces allows white rook
to penetrate on c7.} Nxe5 24. Bxe5 Bxe5 25. fxe5 b5 {Black at last moved this
pawn, but a bit too late.} 26. Rc7 b4 27. Bh3 h6 28. Rf1 $1 (28. Rxc8 $2 Rfxc8
29. Bxe6+ Kf8 30. Bxc8 Rxc8 {does not promise White any winning chances.})
28... Rxf1+ 29. Kxf1 Kf8 30. Kf2 a5 31. Ra7 Rb6 32. Bg2 $1 ({Stronger than} 32.
Rxa5 Bb7 ({or} 32... Rc6)) 32... Ba6 (32... Ra6 $2 {loses a bishop after} 33.
Rc7) 33. b3 $18 {White now threatens Ke3-d4-c5.} a4 34. bxa4 Bc4 35. a5 Rb5 36.
Rc7 $1 Bxa2 37. a6 Ra5 38. a7 b3 39. a8=Q+ Rxa8 40. Bxa8 b2 41. Be4 1-0

