Ra2a3]} Nc5 (17... Rc8 18. a3 Bxc3 19. Bxc3 {[%cal Rf2f3]}) 18. Nc2) 13. a3 {
this move wasn't necessary and is just a lost of time} (13. e4 $3 Nxe4 14. Nxe4
Bxe4 15. Qe2 Bd5 16. dxc5) 13... a6 (13... cxd4 $1 14. Nxd4 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 $14)
14. e4 $3 {Very nice pawn sacrifice. White slows down Black's developpment and
gains the initiative. With the king still on e8, Black is in big trouble.} Nxe4
15. Nxe4 Bxe4 16. Qe2 Bd5 (16... Bxf3 17. Bxf3 $16) 17. dxc5 $1 {Opens the
position} Bb3 (17... Be7 18. b4 {[%cal Rc1b2]} O-O 19. Bb2 $16 {White has
