{[#]} 9. e4 dxe4 10. Nxe4 Bb7 11. Bf4 Nxe4 12. Qxe4 Nf6 13. Qe2 c5 14. Rad1
cxd4 15. Nxd4 Qc8 {As in the previous example, the queen had to go on an
apparently modest square. In the near future, it may go to b7 and sustain ...
a7-a6 followed by ...b6-b5.} 16. b3 a6 17. Nf5 $5 {Being fully mobilised,
White needs to undertake something concrete in order to avoid losing the
initiative.} Bc5 $2 {Weakening the kingside defence will hyave fatal
consequences.} (17... exf5 18. Qxe7 Bxg2 19. Kxg2 b5 $14 {offers Black
reasonable chances to stay close to equality.}) 18. Nxg7 $1 {The start of a
combination in which everything works right for White, even though he might
have not calculated all the nuances from the beginning.} (18. Nd6 Bxd6 19. Rxd6
Bxg2 20. Kxg2 b5 $14) 18... Kxg7 (18... Bxg2 {Unfortunately, Black does not
have the time for this intermediate move.} 19. Nh5 $1 (19. Kxg2 $2 Kxg7 20. Qe5
h6 21. Bxh6+ Kxh6 22. Qxf6+ Kh7 $11 {leads only to a draw by perpetual as if}
23. Rfe1 $2 Qb7+ 24. Kg1 Qe7 {repells the attack.}) 19... Nxh5 20. Qxh5 Be4 21.
Qg5+ Bg6 22. Qf6 {[%cal Gf4e5,Gf4h6] Threatening both Bh6 and Be5.} Be7 {
The only defence.} 23. Qxe7 f6 24. Bh6 $16) 19. Qe5 $1 h6 {The only defence,
which is not satisfactory though.} (19... Be7 20. Qg5+ Kh8 21. Be5) (19... Bxg2
20. Qg5+ Kh8 21. Qxf6+ Kg8 22. Bh6) 20. Bxh6+ $1 {We can notice that in this
game White delivered both thematical sacrifices. They were possible only
because Black took his bishop away from e7.} Kxh6 21. Qxf6+ Kh7 22. Rfe1 $1 {
I am delighted whenever a combination is crowned with a "quiet" move,
completing the development. The threat is Re5.} (22. b4 {was also strong, but
slightly less convincing.} Bxg2 (22... Bxb4 23. Rd4) 23. bxc5 Qxc5 24. Kxg2 $16
) 22... Rg8 (22... Bxf2+ 23. Kxf2 Qc5+ {does not save.} 24. Kf1 Bxg2+ ({If} 
24... Qf5+ 25. Qxf5+ {comes with check, so Black does not have the time for
the intermediate ...Bxg2+ and he loses a bishop.}) 25. Kxg2 Qf5 26. Qh4+ Kg7
27. Re4 $18) 23. Re5 Rg7 24. Rh5+ Kg8 25. Qh4 Kf8 26. Bxb7 (26. Bxb7 Qxb7 27.
Rh8+ Rg8 28. Rd8+) 1-0

