{Text comments by Marin. In this game, play will have a positional character
for a long time. [#]} 12. e5 {Clearing the long diagonal and taking the
control over the dark squares.} f5 13. h4 a4 $5 {Preventing a later a2-a4. Now
and later, Black will place all her pawns on light squares, trying to set up
an unbreakable fortress.} (13... O-O) (13... h6 $5) 14. Ng5 g6 $6 (14... O-O) (
14... Bxg5 $5) 15. Rb1 {[/\ Rb5]} Ra5 16. Re1 h5 $5 {Preventing a break with
g3-g4.} 17. Nh3 Kf8 18. Bg5 $44 Bxg5 19. Nxg5 Kg7 20. Qc1 Qe7 21. Qe3 Re8 22.
Bf3 {[/\ Nh3_f4, Bh5|^] As highlighted by Bronstein, the weakness of the dark
squares can result on a vulnerability of the light squares. But concretely,
the process is not simple here.} Bb7 $2 {Weakening the defence on e6, without
suspecting that this may be important.} (22... Bd7 $5 {/\ Na6_c7_d5}) 23. d5 $1
cxd5 (23... exd5 24. e6 Kg8 25. Nf7 Qf6 26. Qb6 $18) 24. Qb6 Ra6 $2 (24... Nc6
$1 25. Nxe6+ (25. Rxb5 Rxb5 26. Qxb5 Ba8 (26... a3 27. Nxe6+ Qxe6 28. Qxb7+ Re7
29. Qb5 Nxe5 30. Kg2 Qf6 {Marin}) 27. Qxa4 $14) 25... Qxe6 26. Qxb7+ Re7 27.
Qb6 Nxe5 28. Qxe6 Nxf3+ (28... Rxe6 29. Bxd5 Re7 30. f4 b4 31. Bg2 b3 32. a3
Kf6 33. fxe5+ Raxe5 34. Rxe5 Rxe5 35. Kf2 g5 $14) 29. Kh1 Rxe6 30. Rxe6 $14 {
Kortschnoj} d4 31. Kg2 Nd2 $13 {Marin}) 25. Nxe6+ $16 Kh8 (25... Qxe6 26. Qxb7+
{[%cal Gb1b5,Gf3d5]}) 26. Qxb5 {Two important pawns disappeared from the light
squares, weakening Black's structure. But Kortschnoj had to calculate
everything accurately.} Bc6 {Apparently winning a piece.} 27. Qxb8 $1 Rxb8 28.
Rxb8+ Kh7 29. Nd4 {White has restored his blockade on dark squares and the
pawn on d5 remains vulnerable, while the black king is unsafe.} Qc7 (29... Qa3
30. Re3 Qxa2 31. e6 {/\ Nc6+-}) 30. Reb1 $1 (30. Rb4 $16 {Marin} Rb6 31. Rxb6
Qxb6 32. Nxc6 Qxc6 33. e6 Qe8 34. e7 {[%cal Gf3d5,Gd5c6]}) 30... Qxe5 31. Rc8
Bd7 (31... Qf6 32. Rc7+ Kh6 33. Re1 $1 $18 {[%cal Ge1e7]}) (31... Qd6 {Marin}
32. Rbb8 Bd7 33. Rd8 Qe7 34. Bxd5 Rd6 35. Rh8+ Kg7 36. Rbg8+ Kf6 37. Rf8+ Kg7 (
37... Ke5 38. Rf7) 38. Rhg8+ Kh6 39. Rf7 Qe1+ 40. Kg2) 32. Rb7 Rd6 33. Nb5 $18
Kh6 34. Rcc7 f4 35. Nxd6 Qe1+ 36. Kg2 fxg3 37. Kxg3 g5 38. Nf7+ Kg6 39. Nxg5
1-0

