{[%csl Gc6,Rc7][%cal Ge3e4,Ge4e5,Gf2f4,Gd1d8] [#] On the diagram, we can see
another typical Catalan endgame which will be covered in the current lecture.
This situation arises when Black does not manage to carry out the advance ...
c7-c5. Instead, he attacked the centre by means of ...e6-e5. As a result, the
central pawns have been exchanged.  In the endgame, this structure is very
difficult for Black. White has a typical and easy to follow plan at his
disposal. 1) take control of the d-file 2) block the c7-pawn 3) put the
kingside majority into motion by advancing the f- and e-pawns. Without queens
on the board, Black is doomed to passivity.}  *

