{[%evp 0,73,16,-12,-16,-16,-21,-21,-4,-24,-11,-20,-13,-20,3,-27,4,33,17,17,54,
59,61,68,68,8,80,74,68,65,65,53,156,136,156,148,154,155,155,161,151,154,178,63,
56,56,61,50,59,55,53,60,98,87,70,51,70,69,69,65,108,124,114,124,113,89,211,143,
286,301,297,301,309,309,309,279] [#] Let's take a look at another example
taken from the same theoretical variation. In this position, Black played the
more energetic} 10... Ng4 11. e3 Rb8 {As I have pointed out in my comments to
the first example, this is Black's most precise reaction. The idea is to play .
..b7-b5 followed by ...Bb7.} 12. h3 Nf6 $6 {After this passive continuation,
Black will not be able to complete the queenside development.} ({Better would
have been} 12... b5 $1 {when the game might continue} 13. Ncd2 Nf6 14. b3 Bb7
15. Bb2 $14 {In my opinion, White retains a small edge due to the queenside
weaknesses provoked by the advance ...b7-b5. A possible plan would be a2-a3,
b3-b4 followed by Rac1 and Nb3-c5.}) 13. Nfe5 $1 {Once again, we see this
typical idea of exchanging the pieces which stay on the way of the g2-bishop.}
Rd8 14. Rxd8+ Nxd8 15. Bd2 Nd7 $2 {Black makes a familiar mistake. Instead of
immediately trying to activate the c8-bishop, he is trying to exchange already
developed pieces.} ({More logical would be} 15... b6 {[%cal Gc8b7] with the
idea ...Bb7. In this case, I suggest} 16. a3 Bb7 17. Bb4 Bxg2 18. Kxg2 Rc8 19.
Bxc5 Rxc5 20. Rd1 $14 {when Black still experiences some difficulties due to the
weakened queenside.}) 16. Bc3 b5 17. Rd1 $1 {Maybe Black missed this strong
intermediate move.} bxc4 18. Nxd7 Bxd7 19. Rxd7 Rc8 20. a4 Kf8 21. Bb7 $6 {
This dubious move allows Black to remain in the game. Since the remaining part
of the game is not relevant for the Catalan endgames, I leave it without
comments.} ({White should have opted for} 21. Bf1 $16 Ke8 22. Rd1 {[%csl Rc4,
Rg7] When the pawns on c4 and g7 are hanging. Black's position is technically
lost.}) 21... Nxb7 22. Rxb7 f6 23. Kf1 Rc6 24. Ke2 a6 25. Kd2 Bd6 26. Kc2 Bc7
27. Ra7 e5 28. Ra8+ Ke7 29. Rg8 g5 30. Rg7+ Ke6 31. Rxh7 Kf5 32. Kd2 e4 33. Re7
Be5 34. g4+ Kg6 35. Bxe5 fxe5 36. Rxe5 Rb6 37. Kc2 1-0

