{[%evp 0,111,25,-28,-16,-15,31,-1,35,35,35,28,63,32,27,24,24,27,27,9,9,12,12,
22,5,20,18,9,21,21,8,17,77,55,54,49,44,30,46,45,51,51,57,41,39,68,90,65,65,65,
63,61,65,27,27,13,62,81,57,94,124,105,105,86,86,86,74,68,82,56,59,25,92,86,99,
103,103,101,90,105,109,98,126,132,212,212,205,210,215,210,222,222,230,216,264,
270,270,270,270,270,279,279,279,279,388,412,402,402,402,376,608,696,824,908] 
[#]} 20. g4 $1 {Besides Black's queenside weaknesses, White needs to create a
second weakness. Therefore, his uses this typical idea allowing the destroy
Black's kingside structure.} Kf7 21. g5 $1 Rfd8 ({Weakening Black's pawn
structure as} 21... e4 22. Nd2 f5 $2 23. Nc4 {loses the pawn on b6.}) 22. Rc4
$5 Rd5 23. gxf6 Kxf6 24. Rac1 h6 (24... R5d6 25. h4 {[%cal Gf3g5]}) 25. h4 R8d6
26. Rc8 Nd7 27. Rh8 ({Deserved attention at first} 27. b4 $5 {, establishing
control of the c5-square.}) 27... Kg7 $6 {Too passive.} ({Was preferable} 27...
Rc5 28. Rxc5 Nxc5 29. Rxh6 $140 Kg7 30. Ng5 (30. Nxe5 Ne4 31. Ng4 Nf6 32. Ne5
Ne4 $11) 30... Kxh6 31. Nf7+ Kh5 32. Nxd6 Kxh4 33. Nc4 Nd7 34. Kf3 b5 35. Nd6
Nc5) ({or} 27... Nc5) 28. Re8 Kf7 29. Rcc8 Re6 $6 (29... a5 $142) 30. Rh8 Kg7
31. Rhd8 {Threatening Rc7.} Re7 32. Rc7 {[%cal Gf3e5]} Kf6 33. e4 Rd6 34. Nh2
$1 {[%cal Gh2g4]} Ke6 35. Rb7 $1 ({The immediate} 35. Rh8 {allowed} Nf6) (35.
Ng4 $5 h5 36. Ne3 Nf6 $140 37. Rxd6+ Kxd6 38. Rc8 Nxe4 $6 39. Nc4+) 35... Rd2
$2 {Black has missed a simple tactical refutation.} (35... Rd4 36. Rh8 Rxe4 (
36... h5 $2 37. Nf3) 37. Rxh6 Kf5 $14 {was a correct defence.}) 36. Rxb6+ Nxb6
37. Rxd2 Rc7 38. Ng4 h5 39. Ne3 a5 40. Rd8 {The position is now technically
won for White.} a4 41. Re8+ $1 Kf7 ({Or} 41... Kf6 42. Rb8 Nd7 43. Nd5+ Kf7 44.
Rb4 (44. Ra8 $6 axb3 $1) 44... Ra7 45. Rxa4 Rxa4 46. bxa4 Nc5 47. a5 $18) 42.
Rxe5 axb3 43. axb3 Nd7 44. Nd5 {The simplest solution.} Nxe5 45. Nxc7 Ke7 46.
Nd5+ Kd6 47. f4 Nd3 48. Kf3 Ne1+ 49. Kf2 Nd3+ 50. Ke3 Ne1 51. b4 Ng2+ 52. Kf2
Nxh4 53. b5 g5 54. b6 Kc6 55. Ne7+ Kxb6 56. fxg5 1-0

